A Ugandan national who was offering anesthesiology services in Mandera County's key hospital has been charged with being in Kenya illegally.
Mr Ephrem Grace Gengemoi Gum pleaded guilty to the charge and was sentenced to a one-month suspended jail term by Mandera Senior Resident Magistrate Mukabi Kimani.



