The magistrate sentenced the accused to a one month custodial suspended sentence.
“During that period, I direct that the accused be escorted to Nairobi by ATPU officers for the purpose of renewing his Kenyan visa,” ruled Mr Kimani.
The police were ordered to return his passport to him to help renew the visa.
